HEADWORD: Aluminate
<hw>A*lu`mi*nate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A compound formed from the hydrate of aluminium by the substitution
of a metal for the hydrogen.</def>⟦br⟧
